From Don Eller Subject Re MIDI files on MS and SoundBlaster The Cybard wrote I have a computer with a SoundBlaster I'm running Microsoft Windows I have the SB driver set up properly to play normal sounds files I want to play midi files through the Media Player that is included with I know I have to set up the patch maps or something in the MIDI Mapper in the Control I KNOW NOTHING ABOUT This is to be the way I'll get my feet How do I set up Windows so that I can play MIDI files If you install the Soundblaster windows drivers correctly and have the latest drivers the media player should be setup to play files authored to Microsoft's Multimedia midi authoring standard General Midi see the section in the back of the Voyetra manual in the Soundblaster midi upgrade You'll find that midi files exist with all kinds of different mappings so don't expect them to always sound correct without using some kind of midi file editor such as Voyetra's Sequencer You can attempt to use the midi mapper to remap the patches for soundblaster but since you cannot modify the you are allways stuck with the instruments that come with this Unless you can find an editor for making modifications to the instrument settings in I would suggest you locate the early version of soundblaster drivers that were mapped to voices and the later drivers that are mapped to the general midi David Thomas Dudek The Cybard State University ' of New York If music be the food of love Buffalo play on Shakespeare '''